List
----
using []
mutable
store hybrid data types values

eg:
friends = ['Bhanu', 'Ashish', 'Shobit', 'Naveen']

List Indexing

L1 = |7|9|bhanu|rohit|
L1[0] = 7
L1[1] = 9
L1[2] = bhanu
L1[3] = rohit
L1[33] = Error

List Slicing : L1[0:2] = [7, 9]

List Methods: sort, reverse, append, insert, pop, remove, etc....

**********

Tuple
-----
using ()
immutable
store hybrid data types values

eg:
friends = ('Bhanu', 'Shobit', 'Ashish', 'Naveen')

Tuple Indexing, Slicing as same as List

Tuple Methods : count, index, etc....

NOTE: for making single element tuple, it is compulsory to write comma after single element